<h1>@HI{{mada}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

@EM{{@HI{{mada}} V}}

<h2> Definition </h2>

This sentence pattern indicates that something continues to be in the state that it was some time ago.
<p></p>

It can usually be translated as "still" or "as yet".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @EM{{@HI{{mada}}}}@KJ{{rain}}@HI{{ga}}@KJ{{descend}}@HI{{tte imasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It's still raining.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @KJ{{plump}}@KJ{{rice*field}}@HI{{sanha @EM{{mada}} sono kotowo}}@KJ{{know}}@HI{{rimasenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Mr. Ota still doesn't know about it.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

